OL,3,C'The sums don't add up': Leaseholders
OL,4,Cshocked as bills go up 215%
OL,6,FAccording to management company
OL,7,FRealty, the sharp increase will help
OL,8,Ffund "necessary roof repairs."
OL,10,FHowever, some leaseholders worry the
OL,11,Ffees will leave them in debt or force
OL,12,Fthem to move away.
OL,14,FGloria Atherton, 79, has been living
OL,15,Fon the estate since 2012. She says the
OL,16,Fservice charge has gradually increased
OL,17,Fover the years, but this is by far the
OL,18,Fbiggest jump.
